This paper deals with the problem of achieving high throughput in a MIMO broadcast channel with downlink training and channel state feedback. The paper discusses various feedback schemes and their performance, which is a typical problem in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the impact of the feedback channel on the overall system performance, which is related to the field of networking (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of MIMO techniques in the uplink channel, which is related to the field of multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of delayed feedback, which is related to the field of communication systems (cs.COM).
